    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-10T10:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-10T10:25:00-05:00" n="490"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/471: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">George</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-10T18:00:00+02:35"
                            >July 10, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 10—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Foreign Office confirms to me rupture in Arbitration Commission, regarded as
                    grave incident. No confirmation reported war outbreak. Government officials
                    today exhorting public in city streets to give lives for Emperor, mildly
                    inciting against foreigners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
